					<isee:annotation background="#FDF2CD" transparent="true" isee:flat="true" isee:highlight_on_hover="true" popup_corner_radius="1" popup_background_color="#FDF2CD" launcher_label="" show_by_default="false" hide_launcher="false" launch_on_hover="false" x="194.872" y="488.222" width="20" height="20">
						<launcher_image width="96" height="96" size_to_parent="true">C:/Users/Sally.Thompson.MLCSU/OneDrive - Midlands and Lancashire CSU/Pictures/Icons/info blue white fill.png</launcher_image>
						<popup hide_when_editing="true" x="264.672" y="117.722" width="330.334" height="330.156">
							<text>This slider can be used illustrate the impact of alternatives to SGLT2i, or combinations of drugs. Expert judgement is required to estimate the size of those effects compared to SGLT2i.

The default reduction in rates is fixed to the reduction due to SGLT2i usage - if both reach and adherence are 100% then rates are reduced by:

progression - 1380 per hundred thousand
mortality - 470 per hundred thousand

E.g. additional medications may have an additive effect of reducing progression to approximately 3500 per hundred thousand, and mortality to 1200 per hundred thousand. This is modelled by adjusting the slider to 2.5.

Average adherence is approximately 60%, consider reducing this as more medications are added.
</text>
						</popup>
					</isee:annotation>
					<isee:shape x="10.403" y="471.147" width="200.646" height="26.6785" kind="hline"/>
