						<text_box background="#FDF2CD" padding="3" border_width="thin" border_style="solid" x="2.75885" y="69.548" width="461.989" height="482.426">&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;
&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;meta charset=&quot;utf-8&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;
p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }
hr { height: 1px; border-width: 0; }
li.unchecked::marker { content: &quot;\2610&quot;; }
li.checked::marker { content: &quot;\2612&quot;; }
&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:9pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:8pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;The use of&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:8pt; font-weight:700; color:#000000;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:8pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;medications such as&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:8pt; font-weight:700; color:#000000;&quot;&gt; SGLT2 inhibitors, ACE inhibitors, ARBs and diabetes drugs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:8pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt; have been shown to be very effective in slowing disease progression and reducing mortality of CKD.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-size:8pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:8pt;&quot;&gt;Due to the common risk factors for CKD such as diabetes and hypertension, it is likely that a sizeable number of people with undiagnosed CKD may be prescribed these medications and thus still benefit. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-size:8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:8pt;&quot;&gt;The reductions in rate of progression and mortality per patient-year due to increased medication are based on the use of SGLT2 inhibitors. These can be adjusted  to account for alternative drugs, or the overall effect of combined medications, using the ‘medication effect’ slider.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-size:8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:8pt;&quot;&gt;The SGLT2i rate reductions (per hundred thousand patient-years) used in the model are: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:8pt;&quot;&gt;progression: 1380&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:8pt;&quot;&gt;mortality: 470 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-size:8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:8pt;&quot;&gt;An alternative drug may be considered to be 0.8 times as effective as SGLT2i. This would reduce the 100% rates to:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:8pt;&quot;&gt;progression: 1104&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:8pt;&quot;&gt;mortality: 376&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-size:8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:8pt;&quot;&gt;Similar to the primary prevention intervention, these reductions use reach and adherence, and are applied separately to the undiagnosed and diagnosed stocks. Note that typical/average adherence to CKD medication is around 60%, and likely to reduce as more medications are added. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-size:8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:8pt;&quot;&gt;For example, a reach of 50% and adherence of 70% for SGLT2i would reduce disease progression by 483 people per hundred thousand (0.5 x 0.7 x 1380), and reduce mortality by 164.5 per hundred thousand  (0.5 x 0.7 x 470)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-size:8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</text_box>
						<button transparent="true" label="" isee:tooltip="" x="1020.93" y="554.286" width="30" height="30">
							<actions>
								<action target="story" view="5" story="249">navigate</action>
							</actions>
							<image width="640" height="961" size_to_parent="true">data:image/png;base64,</image>
						</button>
						<button transparent="true" label="" isee:tooltip="" x="984.909" y="554.286" width="30" height="30">
							<actions>
								<action target="story" view="3" story="249">navigate</action>
							</actions>
							<image width="640" height="961" size_to_parent="true">data:image/png;base64,</image>
						</button>
					</view>
					<view isee:template_view="template:6" background="white" page_width="1066" page_height="600" zoom="125" type="interface">
						<style>
							<isee:stacked_container item_spacing="0" corner_radius="4" selected_item_color="black" selected_item_background="white" item_background="#DDDDDD" transparent_bg="false"/>
						</style>
						<isee:model_view x="0" y="0" width="1066" height="600" isee:locked="true" zoom="0.45" center_x="1184.44" center_y="845.959" locked_view="true" transparent="true" use_visible_list="true" show_ltm_table="false">
							<model name="Top-Level"/>
							<isee:visible_list/>
							<isee:highlight_list/>
						</isee:model_view>
						<text_box appearance="transparent" x="20.6647" y="117.403" width="505.887" height="434.571">The model also includes the ability to apply costings in three distinct areas:

	- annual cost of primary interventions
	- approximate annual cost of CKD-related primary-care usage and medications per person
	- aggregate annual cost of providing KRT services per person

Due to the nature and purpose of this model, all costs are approximate and should be used with caution. It is possible to overwrite the default values in the &apos;Costs&apos; page.

Costs are based on 2021-2022 values throughout the simulation period (i.e. they do not have an annual uplift applied).

Each CKD stage has an associated average annual healthcare cost per person, regardless of the diagnosis state. The annual healthcare cost for people receiving KRT is an average weighted cost of each modality (based on 2022 proportions). Applying these values to the numbers in each CKD/KRT stage gives an approximate annual cost of providing healthcare. No account is taken of the average healthcare costs for people without CKD.

There is also an annual cost per person for advanced medications (SGLT2i&apos;s and MRA&apos;s), which is only applied to the number receiving these (based on the &apos;reach&apos; slider values - the default values are 20% for undiagnosed, and 25% for diagnosed).

In the Baseline run, these values continue throughout the simulation period. In &apos;Run Live&apos; mode any changes costs or reach percentages are applied from 2025 onwards. Changes can also be made mid-run when running in step-wise mode.





 


</text_box>
						<text_box appearance="transparent" x="592.174" y="337.696" width="424.383" height="83.8436">The annual cost of KRT per person is an average of the cost of each modality, weighted to the proportion by modality in England in 2022.
</text_box>
						<graphics_frame fill="none" x="803.476" y="110.8" width="217.454" height="196.435">
							<image width="395" height="288" size_to_parent="true" isee:transparency="0" isee:fixed_aspect_ratio="true">data:image/png;base64,</image>
						</graphics_frame>
						<graphics_frame fill="none" x="794.663" y="380.16" width="245.007" height="146.632">
							<image width="499" height="284" size_to_parent="true" isee:transparency="0" isee:fixed_aspect_ratio="true">data:image/png;base64,</image>
						</graphics_frame>
						<text_box appearance="transparent" x="592.174" y="146.721" width="188.696" height="124.594">The cost of primary interventions are controlled by a sketchable graph - click and drag to set the cost for each year the intervention is applied.</text_box>
						<text_box x="597.392" y="389.08" width="183.478" height="69.3043">Due to the uncertainty around the cost values per person, it is possible to overwrite these in the &apos;Costs&apos; page.</text_box>
						<text_box x="24.113" y="83.5991" width="259.13" height="22.0794">&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;
&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;meta charset=&quot;utf-8&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;
p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }
hr { height: 1px; border-width: 0; }
li.unchecked::marker { content: &quot;\2610&quot;; }
li.checked::marker { content: &quot;\2612&quot;; }
&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:9pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family:&apos;segoe UI&apos;; font-size:10pt; font-weight:700; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;Costings&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</text_box>
